description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;***Please be aware we have advertised both on Hywel Dda &amp; Swansea bay sites so if an application has been submitted on either side there is no need to resubmit again***&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you looking for your next clinical challenge? Do you want to work in a multidisciplinary Team environment? If so, we might have the opportunity that you are looking for! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking to recruit an enthusiastic and committed Advanced ClinicalPractitioner to join our team at the Amman Tawe Partnership. Working alongside our forward thinking and innovative multidisciplinary team this is an exciting opportunity to enhance your career with scopeandto extend your role as an advanced clinician whether that be nurse practitioner, physician associate or advancedparamedic. The role is a mix of triage, face to face appointments, telephone/ online consultations and home visits. The postholder will be required to deal with acute on the day patients, minor ailments as well as seeing some patients with long term conditions. &lt;br /&gt;As a partnership, we are committed to driving forward on developing an integrated and diverse workforce and are looking for individuals who will support us in driving the vision forward. The current partners and staff have invested a deal great of time and energy to create a dynamic and forward thinking environment, but also somewhere that is enjoyable and professionally rewarding to work in. Daily support meetings and weekly teaching sessions are in place for our clinical staff which either comprises of case reviews, internal sharing of learning or an external speaker and all clinicians are encouraged to support these sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential Qualifications – Advanced Practice Level 7 – MSC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primary Care Experience / Prescribing desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are dynamic, enthusiastic and want to be part of a team delivering excellence in care- then we would love to hear from you?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Why don’t you get in touch to find out more – we always welcome informal enquiries and visits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact us at Ammantawe.partnership@wales.nhs.ukto speak to the practice manager or either of the Partners.&lt;/p&gt;
